<body style="background-color: wheat;"><!--PoemName-->
    <h1>Ozymandias</h1>
    <!--Poet'sName--><h3>byPercyByssheShelley</h3>
    <!--Poem-->
    <p>Imetatravellerfromanantiqueland,<br/>Whosaid—“Twovastandtrunklesslegsofstone<br/>Standinthedesert....Nearthem,onthesand,<br/>ruv01122@gmail.com
    Halfsunkashatteredvisagelies,whosefrown,<br/>Andwrinkledlip,andsneerofcoldcommand,<br/>Tellthatitssculptorwellthosepassionsread<br/>Whichyetsurvive,stampedontheselifelessthings,<br/>Thehandthatmockedthem,andtheheartthatfed;<br/>Andonthepedestal,thesewordsappear:<br/>MynameisOzymandias,KingofKings;<br/>LookonmyWorks,yeMighty,anddespair!<br/>Nothingbesideremains.Roundthedecay<br/>OfthatcolossalWreck,boundlessandbare<br/>Theloneandlevelsandsstretchfaraway.”<br/></p><hr/>
